abstract: The Mexican Minister, Senor MATA, has received advices direct from Vera Cruz by the Saratoga, at Pensacola. The Juarez Government does not authorize the consummation of any treaty at Washington, but signifies its determination to continue the negotiations at Vera Cruz, conclude a treaty there if possible, and if no treaty can be made, they will struggle on as best they can.
